caption.title:
Percentage of high-risk tracts by emission source category and quartile (Q) of median household income (A) and proportion African-American residents (B). High risk is defined > the 90th percentile of risk from each source among Maryland census tracts. Error bars represent SE.
*p < 0.05;
**p < 0.01 using Pearson’s chi-square test to compare each quartile within a source category to the first.
